{
  "_README": "Electrochemical (potentiodynamic) Critical Pitting Temperature dataset for AUSTENITIC stainless steels. Source: Hou F., Wu H.-H., Zhu D. et al., 'Interpretable material descriptors for critical pitting temperature in austenitic stainless steel via machine learning', npj Materials Degradation (2025), DOI 10.1038/s41529-025-00563-0 (open access). 123 records from the article's Supplementary dataset (Table S1), each with measured composition (Cr/Mo/N etc.) + electrochemical CPT + test conditions (Cl-, pH, scan rate), compiled by the npj authors from 13 original sources (npj_ref column maps to that paper's reference list). BASIS = electrochemical / potentiodynamic in chloride solution — DISTINCT from the ASTM G48 / 6% FeCl3 immersion basis of PitCast's primary CPT correlation (data/measurements.json). The two MUST NOT be merged (G48 and potentiodynamic CPT scale differently with PREN). This file powers a SEPARATE electrochemical-basis CPT correlation, reported alongside (never mixed with) the G48 correlation. PREN_N30 = Cr + 3.3*Mo + 30*N. Values transcribed verbatim from the supplementary PDF via pdftotext; nothing fabricated.",
